sources.title: A Cuckoo in the Nest
sources.description: The sexual innuendos fly in this marital comedy of errors set in an small English inn. Tom Walls starrs at the head of a lively British cast that includes a few familiar faces who would make their marks in future years. An adaptation of a play by Ben Travers. IMDB rating 6.0. Directed by Tom Walls. Released in 1933 (UK). Complete print.

sources.title: The Nest | Full Movie | Mystery Horror | Dee Wallace
sources.description:

metadata.Plot: Rory is an ambitious entrepreneur who brings his American wife and kids to his native country, England, to explore new business opportunities. After abandoning the sanctuary of their safe American suburban surroundings, the family is plunged into the despair of an archaic '80s Britain and their unaffordable new life in an English manor house threatens to destroy the family.
